title.narrative: Staff and partners have enhanced capacity to provide timely assistance to programmes in line with office key performance indicators

description.narrative: Partnerships with CSOs remain the major programme implementation modality. 2021 saw 144 active PCAs with 39 national NGOs and 53 international NGOs, with funds allocated totalling US$142.3 million. Funding availability was the biggest challenge in 2021 due to inflexibility of earmarked funding. Two major PBR exercises aimed to ensure that the office remains fit for purpose in delivering results amid funding limitations. By integrating underfunded initiatives into integrated funding proposals, UNICEF provided much needed funding to these sectors. Enhanced collaboration across sections is increasing UNICEF’s ability to reach more children, better, with less. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:11/01/2022
